";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:2:{s:4:"name";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Mark";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:3:"uri";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"http://diveintomark.org/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}}}}}s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"Living in a browser";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:9:"alternate";s:4:"type";s:9:"text/html";s:4:"href";s:63:"http://diveintomark.org/archives/2009/11/21/living-in-a-browser";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:2:"id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"tag:diveintomark.org,2009-11-21:/archives/20091121163616";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:7:"updated";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"2009-11-21T20:19:38Z";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:9:"published";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"2009-11-21T16:36:16Z";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:6:"scheme";s:23:"http://diveintomark.org";s:4:"term";s:7:"unfiled";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:6:"scheme";s:23:"http://diveintomark.org";s:4:"term";s:8:"chromeos";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:6:"scheme";s:23:"http://diveintomark.org";s:4:"term";s:6:"google";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:7:"summary";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"Google Chrome OS is gonna be a hit.";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2176:"<p>(Googler hat off)</p>

<p>I just spent an hour in Starbucks. (My kid is down the street at a Chinese class.) In the past hour, I&#8217;ve checked my email, read news, caught up on the HTML5 mailing lists and IRC chatter, paid two bills, balanced my checkbook, and written this post. Without leaving my browser.</p>

<p>So yeah, <a href="http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2009/07/introducing-google-chrome-os.html">Google Chrome OS</a> is gonna be a hit.</p>

<p><del>Bummer about the whole &#8220;only runs apps <a title="If you don't own the master (key), the master owns you" href="http://www.google.com/search?&#038;ie=UTF-8&#038;q=%22if+you+don't+own+the+master%22+lyrics">signed by a private key</a> that Google won&#8217;t be sharing with anyone&#8221; thing. I&#8217;m not thrilled about the prospect of working for a DRM company. Google was in the DRM business once before; it ended with <a href="http://googlewatch.eweek.com/content/google_video/google_admits_to_fixes_video_refund_gaffe.html">giving everyone their money back, twice</a>. And does anyone honestly believe the first Chrome OS machine won&#8217;t be jailbroken within a week?</del> Update: I&#8217;m getting conflicting reports about whether retail (non-developer) Chrome OS hardware will include a way to run unverified software. I&#8217;m locking this discussion thread until I can confirm this important detail.</p>

<p>On the other hand, computer maintenance sucks gargantuan donkey balls, and normal people don&#8217;t care about root. If you accost a random person on the street and ask them if they need root on their operating system to install another browser, and they&#8217;ll have three questions for you: 1. What&#8217;s root? 2. What&#8217;s an operating system? 3. <a href="http://googlesystem.blogspot.com/2009/06/browser-is-search-engine.html">What&#8217;s a browser</a>?</p>

<p>Still&#8230; if I had root on a Linux netbook, the first thing I&#8217;d do is install Chromium and then spend 99% of my time in the browser. So I have to think that Chrome OS is a step in the right direction.</p>

<p>This is an open thread, but I won&#8217;t answer any questions on behalf of Google.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:2:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}s:36:"http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace";a:1:{s:4:"base";s:63:"http://diveintomark.org/archives/2009/11/21/living-in-a-browser";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:63:"http://diveintomark.org/archives/2009/11/21/living-in-a-browser";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:1;s:8:"xml_lang";s:2:"en";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:9:"








